<br>
&quot;ARES,Lord of War, activities, and preparations of battle. How dare you even attempt to sack Athens, the highlight of Greece? For not only is it the apple of the Greecian eye, it is the patron city of our beloved sister Athena. It is by no fault of her's and leastly the fault of the people of Athens, that Dawnithinia died. If you want to point fingers, blame Thanatos, black lord of death and dying. I, Apollo...&quot; a hand was placed on his chest at this point.<br>
